On December 21, 2021, the President signed three laws. The first law, H.R. 390, redesignates a federal building in Memphis, Tennessee as the Odell Horton Federal Building. The second law, H.R. 4660, designates a federal building and courthouse in Wheeling, West Virginia as the Frederick P. Stamp, Jr. Federal Building and United States Courthouse. The third law, H.R. 5545, known as the "REMOTE Act," extends certain expiring authorities related to veterans' education benefits during the COVID-19 pandemic. The President expressed gratitude to the representatives and senators who showed leadership in the passage of these laws.